- 'Age' in squirrels can be categorized as 'Adult' or 'Juvenile';
- 'Primary fur color' and 'highlight fur color' refer to the dominant and secondary colors of the squirrel's fur;
- 'Vocalization type' includes 'Kuks', 'Quaas', 'Moans', or 'No Vocalization';
- 'Tail flag type' includes 'Tail Flags', 'Tail Twitches', or 'No Tail Flag';
- 'Approach type' includes 'Approaches', 'Indifferent', 'Runs From', or 'No Approach'.
